1 megapixel = one 1024x1024 image

Megapixelsteps = megapixels × steps. Steps are required for image generation and linearly increase the length of a job. For example, a 20 step job takes twice as long as a 10 step job.

1 standard image = megapixelsteps / 20 (assuming ~20 steps per typical image) per second
